metadata.name: DiRex #10
metadata.description: Once upon a time, in a bygone era when the Earth was adorned with lush green forests and meandering rivers, dinosaurs reigned over this wondrous creation with grace and magnificence. However, the integrity of that world came to an end, and a dark and merciless age ascended upon the land. The dinosaurs, in the face of unknown forces that swept them towards oblivion, surrendered and left an indelible mark in the annals of history.

metadata.name: Mustachioed #118
metadata.description:
Who has the chance to have a weird mustache on his face?
Art, personality, politics, religion, power or any other factor has made some mustache models dependent on individuals and takes its name from its first or most famous owner.
Mustachioed is a historical research that aims to link the history of the mustache to the digital world.
Each piece of mustachioed is a ticket to enter this unique world where different samples of mustaches are collected.
Who has the chance to register an outstanding mustache to their names?
We must wait and see.
This research will continue!

Collection of unique men with weird mustaches. Including 13 traits and 473 Attributes.

metadata.name: Annum #7436
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Urban Flow Scribe – Free Edition #15
metadata.description:
Urban Flow Scribe – Free Edition is a preview of the final algorithm.

Urban Flow Scribe is a generative art project that fuses the raw energy of street art with the fluidity of asemic writing. Each stroke emerges from the oscillating harmony of sine and cosine waves, creating dynamic, abstract compositions that echo the chaotic rhythm of urban expression.

Everything is generated with code.
This work uses p5.js library.

metadata.name: Infinite Monkey #1
metadata.description:
"If a monkey is given a keyboard and types infinitely at random, it could eventually produce any text, including the complete works of Shakespeare."

Putting the complete works of Shakespeare aside, how many tries would it take for a monkey to produce the word 'art'?

*If your monkey isn’t so clever (or lucky), the creation might take several hours to generate.

metadata.name: Rite of Passage #266
metadata.description:
In life, we all take different paths, different rites of passage, and while the end is all that's ever true, we will still all view it and experience it in very different ways, like that masterpiece hanging on the wall at the end of our gallery visit. 
  

There are always things that we will never have the power to change, but at the same time, we determine the route, we influence the journey, we can choose the person we want to be. We'll look back on memories, we'll have regrets, and we'll think about what could have been - but unlike this artwork, in the end we won't be able to change the final output by simply pressing a number - so live well and be happy my friends. 

---------------------

Generative artwork by Sykcolo / @sykcoloart

Primary sale proceeds:
50% to Processing Foundation
50% to Savepakistan

Royalties:
50% to the original minter
50% to artist (me)

Press '2' to '4' to see what could have been + increase pixel density. 
Press 's' to save

Details:

150 hand-picked colour pallets (thanks to @SteveMakerspace for colour selection method)
2 Frame types
4 Art types
2 Times of day (light or dark background)

License: MIT

metadata.name: Mending thoughts #53
metadata.description:
These are the seams of my thoughts.

Seams connect fabrics to create continuity between elements where there was none. The seams also represent a forcing and a restriction, a modification in the fabric that brings a rigidity and takes away some of the freedom from the elements.
Some fabrics are sewn with white string, others with red string. The red string represents life (blood) and are thoughts of rebellion against rigidity.

I reused the 21 ancestral symbols already codified in the other projects and I arranged them above and below the seams as elements of asemic writing that represent my thoughts.

50% of primary market earnings will be donated to "Cure Parkinson's".

Everything is generated with code. This work uses p5.js library.

Press S to save the image in png format.
